org.eclipse.papyrus.sysml14.blocks

Interface BoundReference

  • All Superinterfaces:
    EndPathMultiplicity, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BoundReferenceCustomImpl, BoundReferenceImpl

    public interface BoundReference
extends EndPathMultiplicity
    A representation of the model object 'Bound Reference'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Binding Path
    • Bound End
    See Also:
    BlocksPackage.getBoundReference()

      • getBindingPath

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property> getBindingPath()
        Returns the value of the 'Binding Path' reference list. The list contents are of type Property. Gives the propertyPath of the NestedConnectorEnd applied, if any, to the boundEnd, appended to the role of the boundEnd.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Binding Path' reference list.
        See Also:
        BlocksPackage.getBoundReference_BindingPath()

      • getBoundEnd

        org.eclipse.uml2.uml.ConnectorEnd getBoundEnd()
        Returns the value of the 'Bound End' reference. Gives a connector end of a binding connector opposite to the end linked to the stereotyped property, or linked to a property that generalizes the stereotyped one through redefinition.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Bound End' reference.
        See Also:
        setBoundEnd(ConnectorEnd), BlocksPackage.getBoundReference_BoundEnd()
